    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I know this corridor well. Carole Park's buyer pool is distinct: first home buyers comparing it against Richlands and Darra, and investors tracking rental yields in the western Brisbane to Ipswich employment corridor. Getting the positioning right between those two audiences is what separates a fast, well-priced campaign from a prolonged one.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The residential section of Carole Park is predominantly post-war brick homes on generous blocks with practical layouts that suit both families and investors. The Ipswich Motorway connection means commuting buyers can reach the CBD, Logan and Ipswich employment hubs efficiently, and that connectivity underpins consistent rental demand alongside the owner-occupier market. Properties with well-maintained presentation and usable outdoor space consistently outperform in this value-driven market.
    </p>
